RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 11. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAMBO DANCER brushed lightly with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, recovered to lead the field between horses up the backstretch, continued to show the way while racing in the two and three path around the turn and dug in gamely in the stretch to hold the win. KENYA SUN chased the leader on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, began a bid from the three and four path coming around the bend, dueled in the stretch and could not get by the winner. VOODAYO brushed with the horse to her outside at the break, settled off the pace between horses for the run up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground mildly in the lane. PURE ELEGANCE trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three and four path around the bend and improved position in the stretch. ISLA BONITA raced off the pace on the inside early, navigated the turn from the two path and made no bid. WESTLODGE INTRIGUE tracked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, began to drop back while saving ground around the turn and tired further in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAWEETIE GIRL led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled around the second bend, still in the two path, and kicked clear in the final furlong. LA TACHE was reluctant to load, veered out and brushed with the horse to her inside at the break, raced in the two path early, stalked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path and could not go with the winner late, chasing that rival home. CALISUE raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn and was outkicked in the lane. FREE SHOT raced in the three path around the firs turn, settled in the middle of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, angled in to save ground around the second turn and showed no kick. MIGHTY MADI was bumped and forced back leaving the gate, recovered to save ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, began to drop back while racing on the rail around the far turn and faded further in the lane. BRITTY trailed well behind the field the entire way around the oval and despite saving ground was never a factor.

ENTRY.OWNER: Fazio Michael and Sacco Gregory D

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1 1/16M Turf CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Hav e Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BROOKLYN GUY bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, raced in the three path around the first turn, trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, angled in to save ground coming around the far turn, began a bid approaching the quarter pole, switched outside in upper stretch and gained ground quickly to get up late. JAY BIRD saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far bend, kicked clear in upper stretch and dug in but was caught in the final strides. RED OCTOBER raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, navigated the far turn from the three path and gained ground late. BALLINDINE raced in the two path early, tracked the leaders up the backstretch, came around the second bend in the three path and finished evenly. COPAZO bumped with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, raced at the back of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and passed tiring horses in the lane. TUMIGA raced off the pace in the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the four path, swung wide into the stretch and made no bid. CORE FACTOR raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, navigated the far bend from the four path and faded from there. SLICK EVANS led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the far turn and tired in the lane. PRINCE GHOST bumped with the horse to his inside at the break, raced in the five path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, stumbled and lost his rider coming around the far turn, was caught and walked off. AN INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE INCIDENT AROUND THE FAR TURN. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH. TIMES CHANGED FOLLOWING REVIEW.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $20,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOT EM THINKING trailed the field early, began to move up while racing into traffic in the two path coming around the turn, found room in upper stretch and gained ground on the outside to edge clear late. TUNA N STAMPS dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path coming around the bend, kicked clear in upper stretch and was caught late. HEREBY stalked the leader on the outside through the opening quarter, raced in the four path around the turn and kept on to the wire. GREENPOINT dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the turn and weakened in the lane. J J'S JUSTICE bobbled slightly leaving the gate, recovered to chase the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and faded in the stretch. TIMMINS tracked the pace setters between horses in the early going, navigated the turn from the three path and tired in the lane. MAGNA RULER raced off the pace on the outside in the opening stages, dropped back to trail the field while saving ground headed into the turn and was no factor from there.

MISS MIKAELA dueled between horses up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and faded from there. ITSAKEYPER trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, swung wide into the stretch and made no bid. LITTLE RED BUTTON hit the gate leaving it, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLAT OUT COOL stalked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and drew off in the stretch while drifting mildly late. MISS INEZ bumped with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, trailed the field in the opening stages, raced in the five path around the turn, swung wide to began a bid entering the stretch and gained ground late. RAIN OF BLESSING raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and improved position mildly in the lane. THATS ALL SHEWROTE chased the leader on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, challenged from the rail racing around the turn and weakened in the final furlong. SONG OF THE HEART led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the bend and faded in the stretch. SENA THE DUCHESS bumped with the horse to her outside at the start, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and passed tiring horses in the lane. TROUBLE IN RED tracked the leaders between horses up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and tired in the stretch. MY GIRL MELLY raced in the middle of the pack between horses early, came around the turn in the four path and flattened out in the lane. ADRIANA ES BONITA raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the five path and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Sin ce Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUSTIN UP saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the rail coming around the far turn and drew off in the lane. DIAL HIM UP trailed the field on the rail around the first turn and up the backstretch, switched out to the four path coming around the second turn, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late to the wire. STREET GLIDE raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the four path, launched a bid entering the stretch and improved position in the lane. MY BIG DRAMA saved ground early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack, continued to save ground around the far turn and finished evnely. GHOST OF KHOZAN was reluctant to load, raced at the back of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the two path and passed tiring horses from there. CAJUN CRACKER was sent to an early lead while saving ground around the first bend, opened up while racing up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the second turn and tired in the final furlong. URBAN BEACH saved ground around the first turn, raced inside off the pace up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two and three path, ran into traffic near the eighth pole and was outkicked. SOUTHERN CIVILITY tracked the leader from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the second bend, raced into traffic as CAJUN CRACKER tired backwards and flattened out to the finish. NOT A DANCE raced in the two path early, settled off the pace between horses for the run up the backstretch, came around the second bend in the three path and made no bid. WICKED MOMENT raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch at the back of the pack on the outside, dropped back to trail the field on the rail coming around the far turn and was empty in the stretch. TIMES CHANGED FOLLOWING REVIEW.
